<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-04-1305 </DOCNO><TEXT>At Heilbronn the 700 MW branch of the fossil-fuel power plant has startedup in 1985 equipped with a desulfurization plant. Special planning criteriahave to be taken into account: restricted place by flue gas channelsbetween boiler house and e-filter, high wind loads on the denitrificationplant, best architectural design, ammonia storage in a distance of 500m and short planning and construction time. The construction solutioninfluenced by the retrofitting measures are explained in detail.</TEXT></DOC>